                <note rend="inline" type="source">694.113Lumber/122: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Chargé in Japan</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Neville</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1929-11-27T15:00:00-05:00"
                            >November 27, 1929—3 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>120. Your 110, November 26, 5 p.m. Your proposed action approved.<note n="45"
                        xml:id="d280fn45">In despatch No. 165, March 17, 1931, the Chargé in Japan
                        reported to the Secretary of State the action taken by the Japanese
                        Government on March 12 to revise the lumber tariff by increasing Siberian
                        and Asiatic mainland import duties (694.113 Lumber/129). The Japanese Diet
                        subsequently passed the proposal.</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Cotton</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
